column10: What other details can be provided about the church, its architecture, and its roof specifically? Why are the spires characterized as dramatic?
column11: I appreciate that the roof is described as domed and that the description included the spires, but I would like more detail.
column13: The description does not include the level of detail I prefer.
column19: What specific items of tableware are present in the picture?
column21: The description did not contain details about the tableware and focused more on the food than the dishes and utensils featured in the text of the article. It also did not specify if leaves or other foods were part of the tableware.
column22: The description is too general and needs to be more targeted to the content of the article.
column28: Does this image contain any sculptures? If so, where are they in the picture and what are the sculptures?
column29: Description was brief which could be a good thing
column30: The description does not seem to be relevant to the article and does not describe sculptures that are presumably present.
column31: The description needs to include information relevant to the text, including details about sculptures.
column37: The article describes various types of windows that don't seem to be included in this picture.
column38: It was brief and described the window with a bit of detail about the sliding panes.
column39: It could have more detail about the windowpanes themselves
column46: What is a passive mountain slope? What, if anything, can we see of stratification?
column47: Fairly descriptive compared to some others
column48: Unclear what passive slope is. The description needs punctuation.
column55: Are there any other foods on the table?
column57: Given the breadth of the article, it seems there might be more in the picture, but perhaps all that is there is a turkey and wine.
column64: Are there any other details that haven't yet been described?
column66: Initially, the description stated a group of males, but later said two males, so that was a bit confusing
column67: I like this level of detail.
